{"questionId":"7466","questionHtml":"<p>Copper (<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{}_{29}^{64}{\\text{Cu}}\">\n  <msubsup>\n    <mrow>\n\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>29</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>64</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </msubsup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>Cu</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>)&nbsp;decays to nickel (<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{}_{28}^{64}{\\text{Ni}}\">\n  <msubsup>\n    <mrow>\n\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>28</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>64</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </msubsup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>Ni</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>). What are the particles emitted and the particle that mediates the interaction?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/50488b2bc927bbac30c110a1da6e8d1a82a936ee.png\"></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"7466","referenceCode":"18N.1.SL.TZ0.26","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Copper ( 29 64 Cu ) decays to nickel ( 28 64 Ni ). What are the particles emitted and the particle that mediates the interaction?","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"26","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 7: Atomic, nuclear and particle physics","7.1 – Discrete energy and radioactivity","Core","Topic 7: Atomic, nuclear and particle physics","7.3 – The structure of matter","Core","Topic 7: Atomic, nuclear and particle physics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}